I’m not complaining! I’m not attacking anyone I’m stating a fact. And yes you are being a hypocrite read back what you’ve written if it’s slipped your mind. 

I’m genuinely sorry that you can’t see what’s wrong with what you’ve said it must be difficult in life when you constantly think you’re right. 

This conversation is seriously pointless and bringing negativity into my day so please just leave it at this. I’m just stating my opinion I’m allowed to have an opinion it’s served me well so far and I don’t expect to be attacked for thinking a certain way. Please respect that not everyone will agree with you, okay? I understand that you clearly view this very differently from me but that does not mean this side of the situation should be invalidated. Have a good day regardless and don’t reply to this or I’ll block.

You are practically impossible to talk to. Like every other toxic person you attack people for no reason and refuse to accept you’re wrong. I’m not making sweeping generalisations at all. I know some extroverts are nice but some are not I’ve had experience with both so I’d appreciate it if you got down from that high horse and respected that bad people exist.

Dude, you’re literally being a hypocrite here. You are the one whining about other people’s opinions in this entire post, not me. I’m just responding with my own opinion. If you actually knew anything about social anxiety you’d know that “basic communication skills” doesn’t solve squat when being in a room with anyone makes it difficult to breathe. I’m not “whining about how hard my life is” My life isn’t hard I never said it was. This is nothing to do with me. This has everything to do with extroversion please stop attacking my personal life because that’s just plain rude. Accept that I have a different opinion and stop being toxic. Thank you.

Well I’m sorry I have an opinion that’s different from yours really I thought people were past this..  I wasn’t complaining about people every day of my life I just put up with them and hated it so it’s unfair that after a few days we get it in the neck from them because they’re bored and can’t see people. 

I’m not comparing?? I’m not saying that being an extrovert makes them selfish I’m saying that the way they are acting is selfish because they are constantly having a great time while people who don’t enjoy being with people are constantly not, so now the tables have turned for once they just can’t be civil about it. Also, what’s funny...??
They sound like they’re just talking advantage of you.

They kinda deserve it though (at least the ones I know) for every comment they made forcing me into something I can’t do and alienating me finally they have some discomfort with their surroundings. Honestly, I’m really hoping they’ll come out of this and respect the fact that not everyone is the same and some people do not enjoy what they enjoy.
